<section class="section">
 <div class="container container--narrow">
 <h2 class="section-title">Clinical documentation, simplified.</h2>
 <p>After each infusion visit, your office receives a clinical note in a consistent, predictable format. This includes:</p>
 <ul>
 <li>Medication administered, dose, route, and lot number</li>
 <li>Vital signs (pre- and post-infusion)</li>
 <li>Adverse event documentation (if applicable)</li>
 <li>Nursing assessment and clinical observations</li>
 <li>Next scheduled visit</li>
 </ul>
 <p>Notes are returned within 24 hours of each visit. Format is consistent across all patients and visits — designed for easy integration into your EHR.</p>
 </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--soft">
 <div class="container">
 <h2 class="section-title">Conditions and therapies we support.</h2>
 <p class="lead">We administer home infusion therapy for a range of diagnoses. If your patient's condition isn't listed, call us and we'll confirm formulary fit before you refer.</p>
 <div class="grid grid--2 mt-6">
 <div class="card"><h3>Neuroimmunology &amp; immunodeficiency (IVIG/SCIG)</h3><p>IVIG and SCIG for CIDP, multifocal motor neuropathy, and other neuroimmune indications, plus CVID, XLA, and hypogammaglobulinemia. We're built for high-volume immunology prescribers who want to move stable patients out of the infusion center and into the home.</p></div>
 <div class="card"><h3>Infectious disease</h3><p>IV antibiotics, antifungals, and antivirals for conditions including osteomyelitis, cellulitis, endocarditis, and septic arthritis managed post-hospitalization.</p></div>
 <div class="card"><h3>Hematology</h3><p>Iron replacement therapy for iron-deficiency anemia, chemotherapy-related anemia, and IBD-associated anemia.</p></div>
 <div class="card"><h3>Rheumatology and immunology</h3><p>Biologic infusions for appropriate indications per your prescribing authority and plan coverage.</p></div>
 <div class="card"><h3>Hydration and supportive care</h3><p>IV hydration for hyperemesis gravidarum, Crohn's disease, and post-surgical dehydration.</p></div>
 </div>
 <p class="footnote mt-4"><em>All therapies subject to formulary availability and payer authorization. Call {{ site.phone }} to confirm prior to referral.</em></p>
 </div>
</section>

